title: Harmeet Dhillon
added: During the [[COVID-19 pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]], she filed numerous unsuccessful lawsuits to halt the implementation of [[stay-at-home orders]] and other emergency restrictions implemented to halt the spread of the coronavirus. She criticized requirements that people wear [[Face masks during the COVID-19 pandemic|face masks]] (claiming that "the masks don't work"), called for the re-opening of the economy, and criticized voting reforms intended to make it easier to vote through [[Postal voting in the United States|postal voting]] at a time when in-person voting posed a public health risk.<ref name=":1"/><ref name="Politico2020"/><ref name=":2"/>
